The paper deals with developing a fully-dynamic algorithm for maintaining cardinality of maximum-matching in a tree. This involves data structures and algorithms for graphs and trees, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
